        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification gradation 3",
        "description": "Manufactured solution verification or equivalent order-of-accuracy test for the scalar hemolysis transport equation must demonstrate expected convergence rates. Achieved: method of manufactured solutions applied to the power-law hemolysis scalar transport; second-order spatial accuracy confirmed on all mesh refinement levels."
      },
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) was applied to the Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis scalar transport equation discretized in Fluent via UDF. Observed convergence rate of 1.97 ± 0.04 is consistent with the second-order scheme. Results archived in verification report VR-2025-004."
    },
    {
