        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error gradation 4 — GCI < 5% on hemolysis QoI",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) must be below 5% on the normalized hemolysis index at all five operating points using at least three systematically refined meshes. Achieved: GCI ranging 1.8%–4.3% across operating points on a 4-level refinement series (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M, 31.7M cells)."
      },
      "rationale": "A four-level mesh refinement study was conducted following Celik et al. (2008) GCI methodology. Refinement ratio r = 1.45 applied uniformly. GCI on normalized hemolysis index ranged from 1.8% (design point) to 4.3% (off-design high-flow point), all below the 5% acceptance threshold. Richardson extrapolation estimates archived in discretization error report DE-2025-007."
    },
    {
