      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/test-conditions-mrl5",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions gradation 3 — boundary conditions match experimental setup",
        "description": "Inlet velocity profiles, rotational speed, fluid properties (bovine blood, 37°C, Hct 35%), and outlet pressure boundary conditions must be documented and matched to experimental records within stated tolerances. Achieved: all boundary conditions verified against experimental protocol EP-FDA-2023-001."
      },
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA generic pump hemolysis study (Stewart et al., 2012) were reproduced in the CFD model. Inlet velocity profiles measured by PIV at the pump inlet plane were applied as boundary conditions. Rotational speed set to ±0.5 RPM of experimental values. Fluid properties matched to bovine blood rheology measurements reported in the experimental protocol. Condition matching documented in test condition reconciliation report TCR-2025-002."
    },
    {
