        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison gradation 4 — quantitative agreement with uncertainty bounds",
        "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points. Achieved: all five operating points within ±1 combined standard uncertainty; mean absolute error 8.2% of experimental mean NIH."
      },
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements from five operating points (3 LPM/2400 RPM through 7 LPM/3200 RPM). All predictions fall within the ±1 combined uncertainty band (simulation U95 + experimental U95 combined in quadrature). Mean absolute percentage error of 8.2% is within the pre-specified acceptance threshold of 15%. Bland-Altman analysis shows no systematic bias. Full comparison documented in validation report VR-2025-009."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/relevance-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
