        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance gradation 3 — NIH directly maps to clinical endpoint",
        "description": "The simulated quantity of interest (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be the same metric used in regulatory submissions and directly linked to the clinical hemolysis threshold. Achieved: NIH is the standard regulatory QoI per FDA guidance; clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100 L directly applied."
      },
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the regulatory standard QoI for blood pump hemolysis assessment per FDA's 2010 guidance on blood-contacting devices. The simulation directly outputs NIH via the integrated hemolysis scalar transport model. The clinical acceptance threshold of 0.1 g/100 L is applied directly to simulation predictions without intermediate transformation, ensuring direct relevance to the regulatory decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/relevance-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
