        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance gradation 4 — device-specific geometry and operating conditions",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump), same blood analogue or bovine blood, and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope. Achieved: validation data from FDA generic pump with bovine blood across the full 5-point COU operating envelope."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation dataset was generated on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in the COU. Experiments used bovine blood (Hct 35%, 37°C) matching the COU fluid specification. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope of 3–7 LPM and 2400–3200 RPM. No geometric or fluid analogue extrapolation is required, placing this at gradation 4 for validation relevance."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/numerical-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/solver-error-mrl5",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error gradation 3 — iterative convergence and round-off assessment",
        "description": "Residuals must reach 1e-6 for continuity, momentum, and hemolysis scalar; mass imbalance < 0.01%; round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic confirmation. Achieved: all residuals below 1e-6, mass imbalance 0.003%, double-precision confirmed."
      },
      "rationale": "All simulations run in double precision. Iterative convergence monitored via scaled residuals (continuity 3.1e-7, momentum components 2.4e-7–5.8e-7, hemolysis scalar 1.2e-7) and stabilization of NIH monitor point. Mass imbalance across all five operating points: 0.002%–0.006%. Round-off error contribution estimated at < 0.01% of NIH via single-vs-double precision comparison on coarse mesh. Solver error report SE-2025-003 on file."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
