        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form gradation 4 — turbulence and hemolysis model selection justified with sensitivity",
        "description": "Selection of turbulence model (SST k-ω) and hemolysis constitutive model (power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger) must be justified by literature evidence and sensitivity analysis demonstrating that alternative credible model forms produce NIH predictions within the validation uncertainty band. Achieved: three turbulence models and two hemolysis models compared; all within validation uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessed by comparing SST k-ω against realizable k-ε and RSM turbulence models, and Giersiepen–Wurzinger against Taskin hemolysis models. Spread in predicted NIH across model combinations: 11.4% of mean NIH, within the combined validation uncertainty band of ±18.3%. SST k-ω with Giersiepen–Wurzinger selected as best-performing combination. Model form sensitivity documented in report MF-2025-005."
    },
    {
