      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/model-inputs-mrl5",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs gradation 4 — Monte Carlo UQ on all uncertain input parameters",
        "description": "Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation must be performed on all uncertain input parameters (geometry tolerances, blood rheology constants, hemolysis model coefficients, rotational speed) with at least 500 samples. 95th percentile NIH prediction must remain below clinical threshold. Achieved: 1,000-sample Monte Carlo; P95 NIH = 0.072 g/100 L < 0.1 g/100 L threshold."
      },
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 1,000 Latin hypercube samples varying: pump impeller tip clearance (±50 µm, uniform), blood viscosity Carreau–Yasuda parameters (±10%, normal), hemolysis power-law coefficients C and α (literature range, uniform), and rotational speed (±10 RPM, normal). P95 NIH prediction of 0.072 g/100 L is 28% below the 0.1 g/100 L clinical threshold, providing adequate safety margin. Full UQ report archived as UQ-2025-006."
    },
