        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples gradation 3 — sufficient replicates for statistical validation",
        "description": "At least three independent experimental replicates per operating point must be available to characterize experimental variability. Achieved: five replicates per operating point (n=25 total); coefficient of variation < 12% at all points."
      },
      "rationale": "The FDA generic pump hemolysis dataset includes five independent experimental replicates at each of the five operating points (n=25 total measurements). Coefficient of variation in NIH across replicates: 6.3%–11.8%, all below the 12% acceptance threshold. Experimental uncertainty (U95) computed from replicate statistics and propagated into the validation metric. Sample characterization documented in experimental data report EDR-2023-001."
