        "name": "Input parameter equivalency gradation 3 — documented mapping of COU to validation parameters",
        "description": "A documented parameter equivalency matrix must demonstrate that COU input parameters (geometry, fluid, operating conditions) are identical to or within stated tolerances of the validation experiment parameters. Achieved: parameter equivalency matrix PEM-2025-001 confirms all parameters within tolerance."
      },
      "rationale": "Parameter equivalency matrix PEM-2025-001 documents the mapping between COU specification parameters and validation experiment parameters for all 14 identified input categories. Key equivalencies confirmed: pump geometry identical (same CAD file), blood properties within ±5% of COU specification, operating conditions spanning COU envelope. No extrapolation beyond validated parameter space is required for the COU predictions. Matrix reviewed and signed off by lead analyst and independent reviewer."
